-- German Bunds Reverse Early Decline; Italian Bonds Drop Before Debt Auction
-- B y   L u k a n y o   M n y a n d a
-- 2010-10-28T07:42:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-28/german-bunds-reverse-early-decline-italian-bonds-drop-before-debt-auction.html
German government bonds gained,
reversing an earlier decline, pushing the 10-year yield down two
basis points to 2.54 percent as of 8:37 a.m. in London.  Italian 10-year securities declined for a third day before
a sale of as much as 7.25 billion euros ($10 billion) of bonds
maturing between 2013 and 2021. The yield increased two basis
points to 3.95 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
